    "We therefore suggest the following arbitrary labels for distance thresholds: very good (<.05), good (<.1), mediocre (<.15), bad (<.3), very bad (>.3).",
    "In Figure 1, we clearly see that even relatively low values such as.075 already signal a significant gap between the two distributions.",
    "We deliberately chose generous thresholds to ensure a conservative test of our hypotheses.",
    "In other words, LLMs could have passed our test even with underwhelming predictions.",
    "Finally, we set up two baselines for comparison with LLM performances."
